{
  "texts": [
    "The English model was robust, showing similar balanced accuracies for prompts with none, one, two or three examples (P0: 74.1%, P1: 73.3%, P2: 79.3%, P3: 80.3%).",
    "The \"Sauerkraut\" model improved with adding examples but achieved its maximum performance with two",
    "examples in the prompt.",
    "The use of the chain-of-thought approach did not improve performance (Sensitivities: \"Emgerman\" P4 17%, \"English\" P4 63.8%, \"Sauerkraut\" P4 80.9%.",
    "Specificities: \"Emgerman\" P4 75.5%, \"English\" P4 63.3%, \"Sauerkraut\" P4 77.6%."
  ]
}